item.title: I almost left...
item.description: I opened Imgur on boxing day for some light entertainment and saw all the selfies. I was about to exit when I just started scrolling. My thought was "Hmm, a lot of ordinary looking people." And I kept scrolling. And scrolling. I realised, that in all the media and fake perfect lives of social media meant that what I was looking was actually real. Just real people. It was really beautiful. Thanks.

item.title: Merry Christmas from ya boi Figaro (and Moni)
item.description:
Fig has been very stinky and uncooperative this Christmas. But he wanted to wish you all a Merry Christmas.
This unit is 15lbs. Please note how strong I am.
I got into felting a few weeks ago and this is the first thing I made - Mr Hankey the Christmas Poo ornament, made from Fig’s fur.
I made my mom a little Shaun the Sheep ornament (it’s her favorite). Also used Fig’s fur as a base.
Then made my dad a Hungarian pepper ornament…with more Fig fur lol.
This Christmas I thought I’d elevate my chocolate game so I bought an airbrush and bonbon molds. The fillings are passion fruit champagne ganache with a coconut/corn flake crunchy bottom and the other will be a coffee liquor ganache. I’ve never airbrushed before so really hoping these pop out tempered and shiny. I’m using chocolate that I roasted (and stone ground for 24 hours) from fermented beans I got from a sweet cacao farmer named Juan when I was in Puerto Rico. I’m trying to make him proud and hopefully not fuck this up.
Fig keeps eating the Christmas tree.
I forgot to show you guys my Halloween costume this year. I feel like a fucking idiot.
Please accept this double Tobias Fünke selfie.
I’ll try to post more this year. <3
